Dear Betty;<br>
Perhaps itĺs my nature to be cautious of an individual with your writing style. I may just be a victim of the environment I have played in over the past decades. I've read and have analysis so many military, and other liberal, political and anti-government documents over the past years that some words easily trigger certain associations. You mentioned that your name is Betty for instance and Bingo, the last Betty to post on this site was a Dr. betty who is very much an advocate of anti-Vietnam veteran propaganda. A quick scan of the POV site shows that spatz had referred to you or someone else with a similar name several times in his previous posts. <br><br>
However, the mentions, are vague and uncertain, if spatz is referring to an individual, he has been holding e-mail conversations with or someone that had posted before but wouldn't do so for some reason or another. Itĺs those somewhat similar circumstances which we see now reoccurring here once again that trigger the yellow flag in my mind. But when you have been where I have and seen and done what I have there is a very real reason why I question certain things if not for anything but for clarification. But post and see where we go to from there. I welcome a good dialog.  I have quite a lot of respect for anyone that served overseas especially in Vietnam and as I've mentioned truthful dialog is always welcomed and embraced  but individuals that have hidden agendas or other motives I have trouble with. I much better have individuals that are hot or cold as Tom has chastised me for on several occasions, I do see things in Black or white, not warm or in gray shades. I donĺt know if thatĺs bad or not politically correct in todayĺs society, its just the way I am and I apologize if I have done or said things that were wrong in my first reaction to your posting.  <br><br>
